    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                <head>No. 578.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Fairchild</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 15,
                            1880</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 30.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On the 11th instant I received a call from the
                        Austro-Hungarian minister in Washington, during which he stated that his
                        government had instructed its representatives in the Morocco conference at
                        Madrid to endeavor to secure religious liberty and complete religious
                        toleration for all classes in Morocco, in accordance with the proposition of
                        the Berlin conference. I at once telegraphed you as follows: “Support the
                        Austrian proposition before conference to secure religious toleration in
                        Morocco.”</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
